<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ901231-0068</DOCNO><DOCID>901231-0068.</DOCID><HL>   Disclosure Inc. Agrees   To Buy Bechtel Corp. Unit</HL><DATE>12/31/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   N.VNU</CO><IN>MEDIA, PUBLISHING, BROADCASTING, ELECTRONIC PUBLISHING (MED)TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)</IN><LP>   BETHESDA, Md. -- Disclosure Inc. said it reached anagreement in principle to purchase Bechtel InformationServices Inc.   The acquisition would make Disclosure, a U.S. unit ofDutch publisher VNU N.V., the contract provider of corporatefilings with the Securities and Exchange Commission.</LP><TEXT>   The companies refused to disclose the terms of theagreement, which won't be closed until next month. BechtelInformation Services is a unit of Bechtel Corp., the largeSan Francisco-based engineering concern. Bechtel Informationhelps run the SEC's Electronic Data Gathering Analysis andRetrieval (EDGAR) project, operates the SEC'spublic-reference facilities in Chicago, New York andWashington; and fulfills public requests for filings madewith the SEC.   Disclosure already provides public information on 12,000U.S. companies and operates a retrieval service for federaland state legislative, regulatory and judicial documents.</TEXT></DOC>